SIMPLE: indecorous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indecorous
<hw>In`de*co"rous</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indecorous</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Decorous</er>.]</ety> <def>Not decorous; violating good manners;
contrary to good breeding or etiquette; unbecoming; improper; out of
place; <as>as, <ex>indecorous</ex> conduct</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was useless and <qex>indecorous</qex> to attempt anything more
by mere struggle.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Unbecoming; unseemly; unbefitting; rude; coarse;
impolite; uncivil; ill-bred.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indecorously</ent>⟦br⟧
